column5: What's the crappie population like in Lac Suel?Thanks

Gary, We have been going to Lac Seul many years and have caught very few Crappies.....but then again we don't fish for them either, since we go to Canada to fish Walleye and Lac Seul is a "Walleye Factory"! We have however, caught an occassional Sauger, Whitefish, Bass, Sunnies and Crappie & several Northern. RBF
There may be crappies and/or sunfish in Lac Seul, but I have not seen one in over 20 years of fishing the lake.
I may need to hire a guide to show me where the sunny's and crappies hide in Lac Seul... Gary, as far as I have ever seen, they are non existent.

I have seen sunny and even an occasional crappy day fishing on Lac Seul, maybe that is what he meant. Have never heard of a crappie or sunfish on Lac Seul. This year we did catch our first crappie on Wabigoon, don't know why someone was silly enough to dump them in, but not a good thing for an already struggling lake system in my opinion.
